Seminar on Songun Politics Held in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea sponsored an Indian national seminar on the subject of "Songun idea, guiding idea of the 21st century" in New Delhi on August 30 on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Director General of the International Institute of the Juche Idea Vishwanath said in a report that the reality of Korea in which it is winning victory after victory even under the situation where the anti-DPRK moves of the U.S. and other Western forces have gone to extremes in recent years clearly proves the vitality of the DPRK government, particularly, the tremendous vitality of the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that he comprehensively set out the revolutionary idea of Songun on the basis of his insight into the changed situation and the practical requirements of the cause of independence, Vishwanath stressed: Only victory and glory are in store for the DPRK vigorously advancing under the Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the floor was taken by the general secretary of the Central Committee of the All-India Forward Bloc, the chairman of the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association, the secretary general of the Asian Regional Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, the chief of the International Affairs Department of the Centre of Indian Trade Unions and other public figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that the DPRK founded by President Kim Il Sung, has become a beacon of hope of progressive countries and independent peoples, adding that this is the shining fruition of the clairvoyant wisdom and extraordinary leadership of  Kim Jong Il, the great leader of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the banner of Songun the DPRK is shining brightly as an ideologically and politically strong country and a military power bravely frustrating the U.S. nuclear threat and its moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK, they noted, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Absolute is the faith of the Korean people to follow their leader forever. The reality of the DPRK clearly proves the truth of the history that a country can shed its rays and a nation can become stronger only under the guidance of a great leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

Congratulations to Kim Jong Il from Hu Jintao 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, received a congratulatory message from Hu Jintao, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and president of the People's Republic of China, on Sept. 3 on his reelection as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon hearing happy news that you were reelected chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea at the First Session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, I extend warmest congratulations to you
 I believe that the fraternal Korean people will surely continue to achieve new successes in the cause to build socialism of Korean style and realize the independent and peaceful reunification of the country under the leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea headed by you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent policy of the party and government of China to consolidate and develop the traditional Sino-Korean friendship. We will make ceaseless efforts for this in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are convinced that the friendly and cooperative relations between China and the DPRK will keep advancing in the future thanks to the joint efforts of both sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wish your country progress and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And I wish you good health and success in your work.

8-day Film Show Starts 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- The 8-day film show started to celebrate the 55th anniversary of the DPRK.
 To be shown this time will be films dealing with immortal feats President Kim Il Sung performed by founding the DPRK and setting a brilliant example in state building and the extraordinary leadership ability and personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man, who has steadfastly carried forward the cause of building a socialist state of Juche with his unique Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are documentary films on the great life of the President including "The Leader Is the Great Father of Our People" and "The Fatherly Leader with the Working Class" and other documentary films dealing with the Songun revolutionary exploits of Kim Jong Il including "Having the Great Brilliant Commander," "Care Shown to Make Their Lives Shine" and "Legend of Love Created on the Road of On-site Guidance." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cinema-goers will see such feature films dealing with the historic days when the DPRK was founded and the heroic struggle of the army and the people for the prosperity of the country as "My Country," "The Birth of a New Government" parts 1 and 2, "The Nation and Destiny" (serials) and "People of Jagang Province" parts 1 and 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientific films will also be screened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A national opening ceremony of the show was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Sept. 3. 
 Opening ceremonies of the show also took place in all provincial capitals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The show that started on Sept. 3 will last till Sept. 10 at cinemas and cultural halls across the country.

Celebrations Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Meetings of workers and members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea (GFTUK) and agricultural working people were held on September 3 to celebrate of the 55th anniversary of the DPRK.
 At the celebration meeting of workers and members of the GFTUK, the reporter and speakers said they were significantly celebrating the 55th anniversary of the DPRK with the boundless honor of electing again leader Kim Jong Il to the top post of national defence in a historical period when Juche Korea was adding shine to its dignity and glory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the cause of building a socialist state of Juche pioneered by President Kim Il Sung was being unswervingly carried forward by Kim Jong Il, they noted the immortal exploits performed by Kim Jong Il as an outstanding leader and a resolute defender of the DPRK, which would shine in the century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on all the workers and members of the GFTUK to direct utmost efforts to increasing defence power and become patriots of the Songun era devotedly working for the prosperity of the socialist motherland, upholding Kim Jong Il's magnificent design of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the celebration meeting of agricultural working people said that Kim Il Sung is the benevolent father and the great teacher who trained them all as masters of land and the country, finding himself among peasants all his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The revolutionary feats performed by the President in solving the rural question will be immortal with the history of the DPRK, they said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They recalled that Kim Jong Il put forward a policy of agricultural revolution, setting agricultural production as the most essential matter in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, to show the way for bringing a fundamental turn in agricultural production, and has energetically led them to highly display its vitality and validity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on the officials of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea and agricultural working people to fulfil their duty as citizens responsible for the rice production of the country by effecting a fresh surge in agricultural production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meetings were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and officials concerned.

Reelection of Kim Jong Il Congratulated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- A rally of officers and men of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces was held at the Jonsung Square in Pyongyang on September 3 to hail the reelection of leader Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK.
 At the rally Vice Marshal Jo Myong Rok, first vice-chairman of the DPRK NDC and director of the General Political Department of the KPA, made a report which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers extended highest glory and warmest congratulations with boundless admiration and wholehearted loyalty of all the officers and men of the KPA to Kim Jong Il on his reelection as chairman of the DPRK NDC according to the unanimous desire and will of the whole army and entire people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His reelection, they said, was a clear manifestation of undisputed support to and warm trust in him of all the KPA officers and men and people and a revelation of the rock-firm faith and will of the army and people to build a great prosperous powerful nation at any cost on this land to carry the revolutionary cause of Juche to accomplishment under his wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has led the WPK, the state and the revolutionary armed forces along the road of victory over last decades to perform great immortal exploits that will shine long in the history of the motherland and the history of the struggle for the liberation of humankind, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the DPRK has turned into a country of impregnable fortress with self-reliant defences, a military power, which no formidable enemy dare provoke, to strike the world people with admiration, they said this is the precious results of Kim Jong Il's outstanding idea of attaching importance to military affairs and his great Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the KPA officers and men to cherish the strong faith that there are the DPRK demonstrating its might as an invincible ideological power, political power and military power and the bright future of Kim Il Sung nation as there is Kim Jong Il and firmly believe in and follow him in any storm and stress to become heroes with human bomb spirit, combatants with the spirit of self-blasting explosion defending the headquarters of the Korean revolution headed by him at the cost of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally, the KPA officers and men danced merry dances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Evening galas of youth and students were held in all parts of the country on September 3 to celebrate the occasion.

New Antiseptic Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Researchers of Kim Il Sung University of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have developed a new kind of antiseptic which corresponds with the highest standard newly fixed by the World Health Organization and the World Food Program.
 The antiseptic makes it possible to keep food fresh for several days even in sultry season. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With a sour and sweet taste, it can widely be used not only in the foodstuff industry but in public catering establishments and families as a seasoning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The antiseptic promotes appetite and has a good effect on the treatment of bacterial diseases of internal organs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, which is easy to make, has no harmful effect on human body.

Pyongyang Essential Oils Research Center
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Ten odd kinds of essential oils produced by the Pyongyang Essential Oils Research Center are popular in foreign markets.
 Perilla herb oil, Abies oil, pine needle oil, thuja oil, etc. have found their way to China, Germany, Netherlands and other countries of Asia and Europe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The center, located in Taedonggang District, Pyongyang, was founded in February Juche 73 (1984). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, which has competent researchers including nearly 50 doctors and masters, is equipped with hundreds of modern facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has many production bases across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The essential oils made by the center are widely used in various fields including foodstuff, pharmaceutical and light industries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The natural insecticide for flowering plants, natural mosquito repellent and natural medicine for acute bronchitis and pneumonia produced by the center won patents in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The annual production capacity of the center is hundreds of tons.

DPRK Takes on New Look under Songun Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Socialist Korea has changed its looks day by day under leader Kim Jong Il's politics based on the great Songun idea.
 The Yonggwang Street extending from Pyongyang Railway Station to the Pyongyang Grand Theatre has assumed a new countenance with the 55th anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea at hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The motorway has been paved again, underpasses reconstructed for convenience sake, footways covered with colored pavements, service facilities built in round, vaulted, flat, zigzag and other styles and dwelling houses face-lifted &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last decade many gigantic and monumental edifices were built across the country. Among them are the Anbyon Youth Power Station, Youth Hero Motorway, Kaechon-Lake Thaesong Waterway, April 25 Hotel, Academy of Koryo Medical Science, Taedonggang Beer Factory, modern poultry farms, salterns and power stations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nature-remaking projects have been carried on in an extensive way throughout the country. As a result, hundreds of thousands of hectares of land have been realigned as large standardized fields to suit the features of socialist Korea. Comprehensive mechanization of agriculture has been put on a higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of rural villages have made their appearance in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mt. Kuwol, Mt. Chilbo, Ryongmun and Songam caverns and other scenic places have turned into tourist resorts for the people.

DPRK Has Bright Future
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- Papers here today editorially say that the reelection of Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and supreme commander of the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK, as chairman of its National Defence Commission at the First Session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly was an expression of the unquestioned support and trust of the KPA servicemen and the people in him.
 They note that Kim Jong Il, with his extraordinary wisdom and tested leadership, has comprehensively developed and enriched the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung and brought the Party, the state and the army associated with the whole life of Kim Il Sung to a high watermark of their development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that the greatness of Kim Jong Il finds its striking manifestation in the long journey of his Songun leadership, Rodong Sinmun says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His unique Songun revolutionary line and mighty Songun politics saved the destiny of the country and the nation at the crossroads of life and death, made a new history of building a great prosperous powerful nation in the worst ordeals, opened up a turning phase in national reunification and remarkably enhanced the external prestige of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With Kim Jong Il, who founded and has carried into practice the great Songun politics, re-elected chairman of the NDC, it has become possible to further increase the might of the Korean People's Army, a matchless strong army, put fresh muscles into the driving force of the revolution and work ceaseless miracles and exploits in socialist construction in the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will demonstrate its might as an impregnable fortress which no formidable enemy dare provoke as it is led by the great illustrious commander who pursues Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun era is an era of gigantic creation and changes in which the state power is immensely strengthened as a whole to display the dignity of the country to the highest extent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military force is the most important state power in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In view of the essential interests of the revolution, we should set great store by national defence and put utmost efforts into it so as to consolidate the whole country into an impregnable fortress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bright is the future of the DPRK government. The final victory is in store for the DPRK as it has the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il, son of guerrillas of Mt. Paektu, the invincible revolutionary armed forces and the unbreakable single-hearted unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that the future of the DPRK is bright and vast as it is led by Kim Jong Il.

Pyongyangites Congratulate Kim Jong Il on His Reelection as Chairman of NDC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 4 (KCNA) -- At least one million Pyongyangites today held meetings to warmly congratulate leader Kim Jong Il on his reelection as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK at the First Session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly.
 The meetings were held in different places of the city including Kim Il Sung Square and the plazas of the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Monument to Party Founding, the April 25 House of Culture, the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium, the Arch of Triumph and the Three Revolution Exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Jong Ha Chol in his speech made at the meeting at Kim Il Sung Square said that Kim Jong Il's reelection as chairman of the NDC was a manifestation of the unshakable faith of the army and the people to entrust their destiny to him and follow him to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is an outstanding statesman and an extraordinary military genius as he ushered in the Songun era, a new era of the Juche revolution unprecedented in the history of the DPRK, with his outstanding political caliber and rare leadership ability for the past 40 years, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely thanks to the Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il that the DPRK has defended its ideology and system and vigorously advanced the Korean revolution, while achieving one victory after another in the fierce political and military confrontation with the U.S. imperialists and reacting to their hard-line policy with the toughest stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the spirit of devotedly defending the leadership of the revolution is the core of loyalty to the Party and the leader and most ardent patriotism and love for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon all the Party members, the KPA servicepersons and working people to consider the spirit of devotedly defending the leader as the first maxim of their life and struggle and become staunch fighters defending the leadership of the revolution led by Kim Jong Il at the cost of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to exert sustained great efforts for the strengthening of the People's Army and consolidate the whole country as an impregnable fortress, holding fast to the Songun revolutionary line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the U.S. does not give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK and escalates its moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK as proved by the recent six-ways talks, the DPRK will continue to increase its military deterrent force to defend the sovereignty of the country, he noted, and declared: If the U.S. imperialists ignite a war on this land again, the DPRK will deal most merciless and crushing blows at them and inflict an irretrievable defeat upon them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for thoroughly implementing the line of economic construction in the Songun era on giving priority to the development of national defence industry to glorify the DPRK as a great prosperous powerful socialist nation which boasts strong national power not only in the political, ideological and military fields but in the economic field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, and representatives of people from all walks of life in their speeches vowed to absolutely trust and follow Kim Jong Il forever and vigorously struggle to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche. 
 Among those present at the meeting were senior officials of the party and state including Pak Pong Ju, Jon Pyong Ho, Han Song Ryong, Kye Ung Thae and Choe Thae Bok.
